<h4 id="customdomainconfigurationresponse">Custom<wbr>Domain<wbr>Configuration<wbr>Response</h4>



<div>
<pulumi-choosable type="language" values="csharp">
<dl class="resources-properties"><dt class="property-required"
            title="Required">
        <span id="fullyqualifieddomainname_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#fullyqualifieddomainname_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Fully<wbr>Qualified<wbr>Domain<wbr>Name</a>

        <span id="certificateurl_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#certificateurl_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Certificate<wbr>Url</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>The URL for the certificate that is used for publishing to the custom domain. We currently support certificates stored in Azure Key Vault only. While certificate URL can be either
versioned URL of the following format https://{key-vault-name}.vault.azure.net/certificates/{certificate-name}/{version-id}, or unversioned URL of the following format (e.g.,
https://contosovault.vault.azure.net/certificates/contosocert, we support unversioned certificate URL only (e.g., https://contosovault.vault.azure.net/certificates/contosocert)</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="expectedtxtrecordname_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#expectedtxtrecordname_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Expected<wbr>Txt<wbr>Record<wbr>Name</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>Expected DNS TXT record name. Event Grid will check for a TXT record with this name in the DNS record set of the custom domain name to prove ownership over the domain.
The values under this TXT record must contain the expected TXT record value.</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="expectedtxtrecordvalue_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#expectedtxtrecordvalue_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Expected<wbr>Txt<wbr>Record<wbr>Value</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>Expected DNS TXT record value. Event Grid will check for a TXT record with this value in the DNS record set of the custom domain name to prove ownership over the domain.</dd><dt class="property-optional"
